29/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Albanian immigrants will be able to apply for biometric passports in two different cities in Greece -- Thessaloniki and Athens.
The interior ministry announced that the office in ThessalonÃ­ki began accepting applications Monday (March 28th).
Immigrants living in Greece can get the same biometric passports as those issued in Albania.
The ministry plans to open similar services in Rome and Milan.
(Top Channel, Klan, Telegrafi - 29/03/11)
